        "article": "Indian Ambassador to the United States, Vinay Mohan Kwatra, has said India is emerging as a global leader of trusted supply chains. Addressing the IXth US-India Strategic Partnership Forum&#8217;s Annual Leadership Summit in Washington, D.C, Mr. Kwatra said this transformation is underscored by resilient economic growth and structural reforms. The Indian Ambassador attributed this transformation to India&#8217;s domestic economic growth and structural reforms, supported by robust and mutually beneficial partnerships abroad. Ambassador Kwatra also outlined New Delhi&#8217;s ambitious macroeconomic roadmap, projecting a structured path for India to grow into a 25 to 30 trillion US Dollar economy by 2047.",
